verbose_text: High-CHADS2 scores were associated with significantly higher baseline levels of D-dimer and hs-IL-6 than low CHADS2 scores (D-dimer : 0.31, 0.32, and 0.36 mg/L FEU for low, moderate, and high-CHADS2 scores, respectively, p < 0.001; hs-IL-6 : 2.27, 2.48, and 2.73 pg/mL for low, moderate, and high-CHADS2 scores, respectively, p < 0.001; XREF_SUPPLEMENTARY).
